timelineItems.name: New York Red Bulls
timelineItems.text: GOAL: Anatole Abang finds the back of the net in the 8th off a great ball from @TheRealBWP! 0-1 #CLBvNY http://t.co/Re0yueMeMY

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: New York's Bradley Wright-Phillips is credited with the assist. He played it into space for Abang to run onto & finish. #CrewSC #CLBvNY

timelineItems.name: Ainslie Binder
timelineItems.text: Isn't that 3 goals in 3 games for #Abang? #RBNY

timelineItems.name: Nicholas Fedora
timelineItems.text: Lazy defending from Pogatetz there. Not enough to contain that close to goal. At least try to block the shot. #CLBvNY

timelineItems.name: Sandy Canetti
timelineItems.text: Really impressed with the Red Bulls passing. Great team organization #RBNY

timelineItems.name: Little MLS Blog
timelineItems.text: Looked like that was almost a mis-hit, and that’s what likely caught Clark flat-footed. #CLBvNY

timelineItems.name: Eric Giacometti
timelineItems.text: #RBNY applying lots of pressure early on. Attack seems to be clicking with BWP and Lawrence down the left wing #CLBvNY

timelineItems.name: Kathleen O.
timelineItems.text: Was gonna tear myself away from #RBNY in a bit to walk over to Jackson St bridge for fireworks. Don’t think that’s gonna happen now.

timelineItems.name: Austin Moore Farrow
timelineItems.text: Red Bulls playing some ridiculous football. Abang is an impressive talent. Go watch that goal by him immediately. Schools Pogatetz. #CLBvNY

timelineItems.name: Russ Andolina
timelineItems.text: Mike Grella, the American Dream #CLBvNY

timelineItems.name: Marios C Sfantos Esq
timelineItems.text: No matter today's final result, gotta love bold attitude, relentless pressure & exciting play of #RBNY .. Jul 11 stadium better be sold out!

timelineItems.name: Carlos D. Mojica
timelineItems.text: Berhalter showing he still has some moves out there in the sideline. #CLBvNY

timelineItems.name: Owen Green
timelineItems.text: We have yet to see the best from Abang. It's only up from here #killingit #rbny #NYisRED

timelineItems.name: Red Bullazo
timelineItems.text: Kemar Lawrence is faster than you #RBNY

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 16' Kemar Lawrence somehow catches up with Ethan Finlay on an almost-breakaway. Don't see that often, if ever. #CrewSC #RBNY

timelineItems.name: Keith Woodfin
timelineItems.text: Come on Felipe, our club is better than that #RBNY

timelineItems.name: John Corbett
timelineItems.text: I can say I saw Abang way back on April 4 in a #NYRBII game. #RBNY http://t.co/MEvNxDKrA9

timelineItems.name: Jeremiah
timelineItems.text: Is there a better left back in the league this year than Kemar Lawrence? On form I can't think of anyone #RBNY #CLBvNY

timelineItems.text: That was worthy of an Oscar, a Tony and an Emmy for Felipe. #CLBvNY

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: That is ridiculous from Felipe. I hope he gets suspended. #CLBvNY
